headline: Wall Street banks sell final portion of Elon Musk's X debt, source says
summary: Musk's close relationship with U.S. President Donald Trump and prospects of X's improving revenue have allowed banks to offload almost all of the $13 billion they had been holding on their books for nearly two years.  Reuters had reported earlier this month that Morgan Stanley was offering the last piece of its $1.23 billion of debt related to X in the form of a fixed-rate loan at an interest of 9.5% and a discounted price of 97.5 cents to 98 cents on the dollar.
